messages.content: How many licensed games were released for psx? Same game released for different regions count as one game.

While it's challenging to provide an exact count, the estimated number of unique licensed games released for the original PlayStation (PS1/PSX) is around **4,000** [thegamer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0). Although some sources claim approximately 8,000 games exist, this figure likely includes duplicates and regional variations [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4). Keep in mind that the number of games varied by region [thegamer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). For example, approximately 1,300 games were released in North America [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2) [listchallenges](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5).

It's difficult to pinpoint an exact number of unique PlayStation (PS1/PSX) games released across all regions due to re-releases, regional variations, and incomplete databases [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0) [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2). However, here's a synthesis of the available information:

*   **Estimates of Total Games:** Sources suggest the total number of PS1 games, considering regional releases, hovers around **4,000** [thegamer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). Some claim the existence of approximately **8,000** games, but this number is disputed as potentially including duplicates, regional variations, and other non-unique entries [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4).
*   **Regional Releases:** The number of games varied by region. For example, Japan had eight launch titles, with only one shared with other regions [thegamer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). North America and Europe each had 12 launch titles, some shared and some unique [thegamer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3).
*   **Database Size:** A comprehensive database, like Redump, may contain over 10,000 entries, but this includes multiple regional releases, revisions, demos, and prototypes [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1). Removing duplicates would bring the number closer to the 4,000 range [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
*   **North American Releases:** There were approximately 1,300 games released in North America [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2) [listchallenges](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5).
*   **File sizes:** The file sizes of the games range from 100 MB to 2 GB [gamespot](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6).
